00:20:37,193 --> 00:20:43,257
over Wi-Fi? Probably not, right? Not normally. So you have to work really hard on networking,

362
00:20:43,377 --> 00:20:46,639
on figuring out what sort of optimizations at the lowest level of networking you need

363
00:20:46,659 --> 00:20:46,839
to do.

364
00:20:47,309 --> 00:20:51,171
in order to create an experience that doesn't suffer from ping spikes and that creates as

365
00:20:51,591 --> 00:20:58,235
kind of as steady if you like a latency experience as humanly possible. And that's something

366
00:20:58,275 --> 00:21:02,977
where in particular compared to PC gaming we can grow everywhere because almost anyone

367
00:21:02,997 --> 00:21:06,659
has a phone. So figuring out where to put your servers and figuring out how to create

